14-day SHN Once worn, it is locked and cannot be removed until the end of the SHN, where it is disinfecte­d at a return point for future use Has a SIM card and GPS and 4G technology, and alerts MOM if the wearer leaves their residence or attempts to tamper with it Used by workers to report their temperatur­e and health, and to scan QR codes at their dorms and workplaces to report their location If unwell, workers can use it to arrange for a tele-consultati­on service run by the Ministry of Health, typically available within half an hour A feature to display electronic discharge memos for workers who have recovered from Covid-19 was included on July 23 • Also has a heartbeat sensor so MOM can track the wearer ’s health • USB cable • • • Updates with important news and notificati­ons on the ongoing Covid-19 situation FWMOMCARE MOBILE APP • Launched on May 18 after over a month of developmen­t, over 414,000 users
